'''史蒂芬·阿诺德·梅特卡夫'''（{{lang-en|'''Stephen Arnold Metcalf'''}}，{{bd|1927年|10月23日|2014年|6月7日|catIdx=Metcalf}}），生於[[云南|云南]][[昆明|昆明]]，是一位基督[[新教|新教]][[传教士|传教士]]，後在日本传教。他是在华传教士[[王怀仁|王怀仁]]（{{lang|en|George E. Metcalf}}）与伊麗莎白·瑪麗·唐納利（{{lang|en|Elizabeth Mary Donnelly}}）的兒子，後來承父业加入前身爲[[内地会|内地会]]的[[海外基督使团|海外基督使团]]，獲使团委派往日本传教。他还有一个同样身为传教士的姐姐，名叫露丝（{{lang|en|Ruth Metcalf}}）。她則在泰国传教。<ref name="Crickets"/>

==在华期间==
{{See Also|樂道院|埃里克·利德爾}}
於1927年10月23日，史蒂芬·梅特卡夫在中国[[云南|云南]][[昆明|昆明]]出生。他和姐姐露丝一起在[[山东|山东]][[烟台|烟台]]的内地会子弟学校[[芝罘学校|芝罘学校]]（又名中國內地會學校）接受教育。[[中国抗日战争|中日战争]]爆发后，日军占领了烟台，于1942年10月5日迫使学校关闭，将学校工作人员、教师与学生囚禁在位于烟台[[毓璜顶|毓璜顶]]（{{lang|en|Temple Hill}}）的[[美國長老會|美國長老會]]差會集中營（{{lang|en|American Presbyterian Mission compound}}）。<ref name=Guardian040112>{{cite news |url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/2012/jan/04/50-stunning-olympic-moments-eric-liddell?newsfeed=true |newspaper=The Guardian |date=4 January 2012 |first=Simon |last=Burnton |title=50 stunning Olympic moments: No8 Eric Liddell's 400 metres win, 1924}}</ref>时年15岁的史蒂芬也被囚禁在其中，且与姐姐露丝、父母都失去联系。<ref>{{cite book |first = Mel | last = Watman | year = 2006 | title = All-Time Greats of British Athletics | publisher = SportsBooks Ltd | location = Cheltenham, United Kingdom | page = 17}}</ref>

1943年9月，史蒂芬随毓璜顶俘虜集中营迁往山东[[潍坊|潍坊]]的[[乐道院|乐道院]]集中营（卽[[濰縣集中營|濰縣集中營]]，{{lang|en|Weihsien Compound}}）。<ref>{{cite book | first = Sally| last = Magnusson | year = 1981 | title = The Flying Scotsman, A Biography| url = https://archive.org/details/flyingscotsman0000magn| publisher=Quartet Books | location = New York, NY, USA | page = [https://archive.org/details/flyingscotsman0000magn/page/150 150]}}.</ref>史蒂芬在濰縣集中營见到了奥运会长跑金牌得主[[李爱锐|李爱锐]]（{{lang|en|Eric Henry Liddell}}），并受其幫助照料。<ref>{{cite book |first = Mel | last = Watman | year = 2006 | title = All-Time Greats of British Athletics | publisher = SportsBooks Ltd | location = Cheltenham, United Kingdom | page = 16}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |newspaper=The Scotsman |date=3 September 2000 |title=Thrilled to follow in Liddell’s footsteps |url=http://www.scotsman.com/sport/football/top-football-stories/thrilled-to-follow-in-liddell-s-footsteps-1-462308}}</ref>李爱锐侭管被日军抓捕投至集中营<ref>[http://www.reuters.com/article/olympicsNews/idUSSP27753620080806 Chariots of Fire's Liddell, a Chinese hero?] {{Wayback|url=http://www.reuters.com/article/olympicsNews/idUSSP27753620080806 |date=20090221083700 }} – By Nick Mulvenney (6 August 2008) Reuters</ref>，但保持乐观、坚持布道，仍爲日本人祷告，这深刻影响了史蒂芬。<ref>Emiko Yuki. ''Take the Torch Shining in the Dark''. Inochi no Kotobashya. 2005. ISBN 4-264-02334-3</ref>1945年，李爱锐因腦腫瘤病逝，死前将自己的跑鞋赠予史蒂芬。<ref>[http://trove.nla.gov.au/ndp/del/article/69059792 British 100 yards record equalled] {{Wayback|url=http://trove.nla.gov.au/ndp/del/article/69059792 |date=20140404105330 }} ''[[The_Advocate_(Australia)|The Advocate]]'' 6 August 1946</ref>当年2月，李爱锐的葬礼在集中营中举行<ref>{{cite book | first = Sally| last = Magnusson | year = 1981 | title =The Flying Scotsman, A Biography | url = https://archive.org/details/flyingscotsman0000magn| publisher=Quartet Books | location = New York, NY, USA | pages = [https://archive.org/details/flyingscotsman0000magn/page/123 123]–32}}.</ref>，史蒂芬是其护柩人（抬棺人）<ref>{{cite book |last=Lovesey |first=Peter |title=The Official Centenary History of the Amateur Athletic Association |url=https://archive.org/details/officialcentenar0000love |publisher=Guinness Superlatives Ltd |location=Enfield, Great Britain |year=1979 |page=[https://archive.org/details/officialcentenar0000love/page/77 77]|isbn=0-900424-95-8}}</ref>，他在葬礼上许诺将前往日本传教，这正是受到了李爱锐的影响的结果。<ref>{{cite book | first = Ronald | last = Clements | year = 2010 | title = In Japan the Crickets Cry| url = https://archive.org/details/injapancricketsc0000clem | publisher = Monarch Publications | location = Oxford | id =}}</ref><ref>{{cite book | first = Sally| last = Magnusson | year = 1981 | title =The Flying Scotsman, A Biography| url = https://archive.org/details/flyingscotsman0000magn| publisher=Quartet Books Inc.| location =New York, NY}} p. 160-170</ref>

1945年8月14日，日本天皇宣布投降；8月17日，潍县集中营解放，至此史蒂芬纔得以与家人团聚。<ref>{{Cite web | title = The Official Report of the Games of the 8th Olympiade | location = Paris, FR | page = 107 | url = http://www.la84foundation.org/6oic/OfficialReports/1924/1924part1.pdf | format = [[PDF|PDF]] | accessdate = 21 April 2011 | year = 1924 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20110505163114/http://www.la84foundation.org/6oic/OfficialReports/1924/1924part1.pdf | archive-date = 2011-05-05 | dead-url = yes }}</ref>

==澳洲深造==
1945年11月，史蒂芬抵达澳大利亚，在[[墨尔本圣经学院|墨尔本圣经学院]]（{{lang|en|Melbourne Bible College}}）学习。1952年，史蒂芬得以加入[[海外基督使团|海外基督使团]]（前身爲[[内地会|内地会]]），被派往日本传教。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.omf.org/omf/japan/resources/stories/japan_revisited |title=Japan Revisited - Steve Metcalf - OMF |accessdate=2013-11-16 |archive-date=2013-04-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130415094743/http://www.omf.org/omf/japan/resources/stories/japan_revisited |dead-url=no }}</ref>

==前往日本==
1952年11月，史蒂芬抵达日本，开始在[[本州岛|本州岛]]的[[轻井泽町|轻井泽町]]（日语：{{lang|ja|軽井沢町}}）接受语言培训。次年，他受命到青森县（日语：{{lang|ja|青森県}}）传教及主持建造教堂。

1957年7月3日，史蒂芬与伊芙琳·罗宾逊（{{lang|en|Evelyn Robinson}}）成婚。伊芙琳是来自北爱尔兰的传教士。他们共育有四子一女。

往後的日子裏，史蒂芬与伊芙琳又受命整合、建造了多座教堂，地域包括青森县各镇，[[北海道|北海道]][[小樽市|小樽市]]、本州[[八户市|八户市]]、[[仙台市|仙台市]]及[[千葉縣|千葉]][[浦安市|浦安市]]。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.theage.com.au/news/world/a-forgiving-man-in-an-unforgiving-war-camp/2005/08/17/1123958126884.html |title=A forgiving man in an unforgiving war camp - World - theage.com.au |accessdate=2013-11-16 |archive-date=2014-03-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140309081908/http://www.theage.com.au/news/world/a-forgiving-man-in-an-unforgiving-war-camp/2005/08/17/1123958126884.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

==返回英国==
1990年8月，史蒂芬结束了70余年的传教生活，之後在位于伦敦的日本[[基督徒团契|基督徒团契]]组织裏又活动了15年。<ref>[http://stephenmetcalfemp.blogspot.hk/2013/10/stephen-metcalfe-mp-supports-biggest.html Stephen Metcalfe MP supports biggest Japanese cultural event in Essex]{{dead link|date=2017年12月 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>

2005年，史蒂芬曾在潍县集中营解放60周年时爲李爱锐撰写悼词。<ref>{{cite news |newspaper=The Scotsman |date=1 December 2002 |title=Eric Liddell – Scotland's most popular sporting hero |url=http://www.scotsman.com/sport/eric-liddell-scotland-s-most-popular-sporting-hero-1-1379828 |accessdate=2013-11-16 |archive-date=2013-10-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131012033931/http://www.scotsman.com/sport/eric-liddell-scotland-s-most-popular-sporting-hero-1-1379828 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=2 December 2002 |accessdate=14 April 2012 |title=Scottish Athletes Prominent in Hall of Fame |url=http://www.scottishathletics.org.uk/index.php?p=17&itemType=news&itemId=29 |series=Scottish Athletics |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131005000238/http://www.scottishathletics.org.uk/index.php?p=17&itemType=news&itemId=29 |archive-date=2013-10-05 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>

